African Christian Democratic Party (ACDP) leader Reverend Kenneth Meshoe. JOHANNESBURG - Leader of the African Christian Democratic Party Kenneth Meshoe confirmed on Friday that he has tested positive for the novel coronavirus. READ: Angus Buchan, wife test positive for COVID-19 Meshoe was tested last week Sunday after attending a religious gathering which included seven visitors from abroad, five have subsequently tested positive for COVID-19. Christian evangelist Angus Buchan was also amongst the attendees and announced he had tested positive on Thursday. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs